resources.string:
 You can save executable code on any server in the .dex file format and run it using this application.
\n The .dex format can be obtained from files in the .class format or from files in the .jar format, when compiling a project in Android Studio, the .dex files of all classes automatically are saved in the /app/build/intermediates/project_dex_archive/
\n At the bottom of this screen is a ConstraintLayout named myLayout, you can refer to it from code and output information to it, for example you can generate programmatically TextView and place it on this myLayout.
\n You can view the contents of the .dex file using jadx app or similar
\n\n Example of code in .dex:
\n\n package com.romankryvolapov.runningfromdexfile;
\n public class Test {
\n   public void test() {
\n     ;MainActivity.myTextView.setText("123");
\n     MainActivity.myLayout.removeAllViews();
\n     MainActivity.myLayout.addView(MainActivity.myTextView);
\n   }
\n }
